    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-11-07T18:52:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-11-07T18:52:00-05:00" n="438"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d438">
                <head>438. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in the Philippines</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d438fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 711.56396/11–157. Secret. Drafted in <gloss target="#t_SPA1"
                            >SPA</gloss>, cleared in draft by <persName corresp="#p_QDA1"
                            >Quarles</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MJG1">Mein</persName>, and
                        approved by <persName corresp="#p_JHP1">Jones</persName>. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPAC1">CINCPAC</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CINCPAC1"
                            >CINCPAC</gloss> for <gloss target="#t_POLAD1">POLAD</gloss>, <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPACFLT1">CINCPACFLT</gloss>, CINCPACAF, <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCPACREPPHIL1">CINCPACREPPHIL</gloss>, <gloss
                            target="#t_COMNAVPHIL1">COMNAVPHIL</gloss>, and 13th Air Force.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-11-07T18:52:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1957—6:52 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1511. Joint State–Defense message. Manila’s 1653,<note n="2" xml:id="d438fn2">
                        <ref target="#d437">
                            <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note> 450, 449,<note n="3" xml:id="d438fn3">See <ref target="#d437fn2"
                            >footnote 2, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                        </ref>
                    </note> Department’s 649.<note n="4" xml:id="d438fn4">Dated August 29, not
                        printed. (Department of State, Central Files, 711.56396/8–257)</note>
                    Appreciate your views on probability early resumption base negotiations if
                        <persName corresp="#p_GCP1">Garcia</persName> administration returned to
                    power. We agree fully that US interests best served by playing down new
                    discussions as much as possible and by avoiding at all costs sending any US
                    special delegation which would focus press attention and ensure reactivation of
                    Philippine panel.</p>
                <p>You therefore authorized inform Serrano US wants discuss bases questions through
                    normal diplomatic channels between Embassy Manila, and Philippine Department
                    Foreign Affairs and would appreciate Philippine agreement to this procedure. As
                    to timing of such approach Department suggests you may wish in line second
                    paragraph your telegram defer until after elections.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FYI1">FYI</gloss>: We agree your idea that as required experts
                    and technicians from Department or Defense could properly be temporarily
                    assigned as advisers to Embassy staff. End <gloss target="#t_FYI1"
                    >FYI</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
